<tt>Mon Jan  6 22:40:41 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Just a quick follow-up to Andy's last (do you prefer Nick or Andy?):  PF's (which most of us thought were more useless than &quot;regular&quot; ARVN's) saved our ass around Christmas, '68.  Nine of us guarding a little piss-ant bridge on the road to Hill 55, and more scattered up and down the road at other possible weak points.  Got hit about 2 am by 60 + VC.  The PF's just to our north were probably the main target - they'd just gotten M-16's so it was probably a VC re-supply mission.  They stuck with it, and we kicked some major ass - 16 VC bodies and only 2 PF's slightly wounded.  None of us got hurt, but it was sure fast and furious for awhile - RPG's, machine guns, you know the drill.  Anyway, I never bad-mouthed 'em again.<br><br>
By the way, some of those guys (officers even) came to me after that to get me to stop a 6 by so they could catch a ride (they knew the US drivers wouldn't stop if they tried to hitch on their own).  I did it, but the US driver wasn't none too happy about giving a lift to our allies.  Hell of a way to fight the war.
<p><code>-- miketol@mtco.com  (Mike Toliver) </code><p>


